Zest the @lime{1} then chop into wedges. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all).

Trim the @pak choi{150%g} then thinly slice widthways.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Peel and grate the @ginger{1/2}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat.

When hot, add the ginger, the bok choy and the red pepper.

Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the veggies begin to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @Thai style spice mix{1} (add less if you don't like heat!) and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the pan is getting dry.

Add the @king prawns{150%g} and stir-fry until cooked, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Squeeze the pouch of @steamed brown basmati rice{1} and tear open. Stir the rice into the pan and stir-fry for another ~{2-3%minutes} until piping hot, breaking it up with your #spoon{}.

Remove the pan from the heat and stir through the lime zest and half the coriander.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Serve the Thai prawn rice in #bowls{} finished with a sprinkling of the remaining coriander.

Top with the lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!